guidance.title: Guidance
guidance.details: If this PV iocvmesvt:watchdog is Disconnected, iocvmesvt is likely crashed and needs rebooting. Refer to the "Web Guidance" entry in the dropdown menu for this alarm for details. Contact SVT expert if problem persists.

guidance.title: Guidance
guidance.details: One of the SVT HV/LV supplies received an inhibit signal. To clear it, click the "Clear All Inhibits" button on the SVT Inhibits screen, accessible from the dropdown menu for this alarm or the SVT Overview -> Hard Interlocks. If the problem persists, contact the SVT Expert.

guidance.title: Guidance
guidance.details: One of the SVT readout chips is reporting zero scalers, indicating a likely latch up. Carefully check the SVT monitoring data in clas12mon. If data is missing, rebooting svt1 and svt2 may be necessary. For details, see the web guidance in the dropdown menu for this alarm.

guidance.title: Guidance
guidance.details: Try to restart the gas flow. ***Note, if gas flow was stopped, the interlock should need to be reset and then HV restored. If problem persists, contact the CVTExpert.

guidance.title: Guidance
guidance.details: If this alarm is MAJOR, check the FMT gas and restart the FMT gas flow if necessary (by clicking "Start"). If problem persists, contact the Hall B Engineering On-Call.

guidance.title: Guidance
guidance.details: If alarm persists, contact MicroMega expert.

guidance.title: Guidance
guidance.details: One of the MVT interlocks has tripped. The interlock will need to be reset, and possibly HV/LV restored. If the cause of the interlock was interrupted gas flow, gas flow will need to be resumed first. If problem persists, contact the CVT expert.

guidance.title: Guidance
guidance.details: One of the MVT software interlocks is bypassed. Consult with the CVT expert.

guidance.title: Guidance
guidance.details: Check the MVT overview screen for HV status, make a logbook entry, and, if a channel tripped or is OFF try to turn it back on. If problem persists, contact the CVT expert.
